article.description: — Tyrese Jenkins had 17 points as Norfolk State beat Bowling Green 90-84 on Friday.
article.headline: Jenkins leads Norfolk State over Bowling Green 90-84
article.linkText: Jenkins leads Norfolk State over Bowling Green 90-84
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio -- — Tyrese Jenkins had 17 points as Norfolk State beat Bowling Green 90-84 on Friday. Joe Bryant Jr. added 16 points for the Spartans, while Kris Bankston chipped in 15. Jenkins hit 5 of 6 3-pointers. Bankston also had nine rebounds. Jalen Hawkins had 13 points for Norfolk State (5-0). Myron Gordon had 19 points for the Falcons (1-3). Trey Diggs added 17 points. Daeqwon Plowden had 14 points and three blocks. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
